Function Reference/wp validate auth cookie « WordPress Codex
-----------

Validates authentication cookie.

The checks include making sure that the authentication cookie is set and
pulling in the contents (if \$cookie is not used). Makes sure the cookie
is not expired. Verifies the hash in cookie is what is should be and
compares the two.

Parameters
----------

 `$cookie` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. If used, will validate contents instead of
    cookie's
    Default:

 `$scheme` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. The cookie scheme to use: auth, secure\_auth,
    or logged\_in
    Default:

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(bool)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   int

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

Source File
-----------

wp\_validate\_auth\_cookie() is located in `wp-includes/pluggable.php`

